{
  "stem": "1857.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I hope that something rubbed off of on my children, and I think it did.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So as far as Jewish life, religiously, I wouldn't say very pious.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But nationalistically, yes, we were-- we were very Jewish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All the holidays.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, the seders were unforgettable.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The whole family came together.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We always had somebody for a Friday night dinner-- outsiders, or-- or poor relatives, or whoever.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Friday night was-- my father came home from-- from his business and ate dinner.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And after dinner, he went back to the business.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But he always had dinner with us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father was [NON-ENGLISH] every morning, but he never went on Saturday to temple.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this was sort of an odd way of-- I think his [NON-ENGLISH] was sort of superstitious.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He wouldn't leave home unless he did it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the Jewish life was-- was very much there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, you know, if you live in a country that is anti-Semitic, and you're being persecuted from time to time, you become more Jewish.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Do you remember any incidences after Hitler's rise to power in 1933 that life changed or anything started changing?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not really.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Polish government, until 1935, there was a dictator by name of Pilsudski, who was-- Joseph Pilsudski was a marshal in the Polish Army.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was sort of protective of the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we felt fairly secured while he was alive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When he died in 1935, we started feeling pressures-- governmental pressures on Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were coming out with all kind of laws as far as kashrut was concerned.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, they were mostly laws-- anti-Jewish laws.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we felt that-- that this government may do something drastic as far as Jews were concerned.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We always were very unsure of ourselves.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
